fable /ˈfeɪbəl/

(fables) 

1. N-VAR A fable is a story which teaches a moral lesson. Fables sometimes have animals as the main characters. 寓言 

例： ...the fable of the tortoise and the hare. …乌龟和兔子的寓言。 

2. N-VAR You can describe a statement or explanation that is untrue but that many people believe as fable . 谣传 

例： Is reincarnation fact or fable? 转世投胎是事实还是谣传？

